<$fill $name="body">

For live interactive examples, see the [[demo wiki|https://rimir-cc.github.io/tw-demo/]].

!! Basic graph

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="A" label="Node A" color="CornflowerBlue"/>
  <$node $tiddler="B" label="Node B" color="Coral"/>
  <$node $tiddler="C" label="Node C" color="MediumSeaGreen"/>
  <$edge $from="A" $to="B"/>
  <$edge $from="B" $to="C"/>
  <$edge $from="A" $to="C" stroke="dashed"/>
</$graph>
```

!! Node shapes

```
<$graph physics="no">
  <$node $tiddler="a" label="dot (default)" $pos="0,0"/>
  <$node $tiddler="b" label="box" shape="box" $pos="200,0" color="Wheat"/>
  <$node $tiddler="c" label="diamond" shape="diamond" $pos="400,0" color="Plum"/>
  <$node $tiddler="d" label="triangle" shape="triangle" $pos="100,150" color="LightCoral"/>
  <$node $tiddler="e" label="star" shape="star" $pos="300,150" color="Gold"/>
  <$node $tiddler="f" label="hexagon" shape="hexagon" $pos="500,150" color="PaleGreen"/>
</$graph>
```

!! Properties cascade

```
<$graph>
<$properties $for="nodes" color="LightGray" size="20">
<$properties $filter="[tag[important]]" color="Crimson" size="35">
<$properties $for="edges" color="Silver">
  <$node $tiddler="Hub" label="Hub"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Leaf1" label="Leaf 1"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Leaf2" label="Leaf 2"/>
  <$edge $from="Hub" $to="Leaf1"/>
  <$edge $from="Hub" $to="Leaf2"/>
</$properties>
</$properties>
</$properties>
</$graph>
```

!! Interactive clusters

Enable with `clusterData` graph property. Each graph can use its own config tiddler.

```
<$graph physics="no">
<$properties.persistent $dataTiddler="$:/config/my-positions">
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/config/my-clusters">
<$properties $for="nodes" color="SteelBlue">
  <$node $tiddler="Alice" label="Alice" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="Bob" label="Bob" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="Carol" label="Carol" $pos=<<pos>>/>
</$properties>
</$properties>
</$properties.persistent>
</$graph>
```

# Drag ''Alice'' onto ''Bob'' → creates "Cluster #1"
# Drag ''Carol'' onto the cluster → adds her
# Double-click cluster label → rename and pick a color
# Drag a node far away (200+ px) → removes it from cluster

!! Separate cluster configs

Two graphs with independent cluster configs but shared positions:

```
<%-- Graph A --%>
<$graph physics="no">
<$properties.persistent $dataTiddler="$:/config/shared-positions">
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/config/graph-a/clusters">
  ...
</$properties>
</$properties.persistent>
</$graph>

<%-- Graph B --%>
<$graph physics="no">
<$properties.persistent $dataTiddler="$:/config/shared-positions">
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/config/graph-b/clusters">
  ...
</$properties>
</$properties.persistent>
</$graph>
```

!! Static clusters (declarative)

For hardcoded grouping without drag-drop interaction, set `cluster` directly on `<$node>`. Container nodes use the `__cluster__` prefix:

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="__cluster__Engineering" label="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Frontend" label="Frontend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Backend" label="Backend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering"/>
  <$edge $from="Frontend" $to="Backend"/>
</$graph>
```

